    "causal_summary": "After 015 fixed the dominant RRF-vs-cosine miscalibration, on-topic searches still under-report: generic 2–3 word queries read `weak`/`donotcite` despite mixed-but-relevant matches, a strong top hit is dragged down by a weaker tail, token-budget truncation hides results (5→1), and weak models render non-comparable output fields (`confidence` vs `similarity`) across surfaces",
